This paper is about incorporating commonsense knowledge into language representation models, which is a topic related to natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a pre-training approach and investigates different pre-training tasks, which are related to machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), making cs.LG a likely sub-category as well. The paper also evaluates the performance on various NLP tasks, such as sentence classification and natural language inference (NLI) tasks, which are related to information retrieval (IR) and computational linguistics (CL), making cs.IR and cs.CC likely sub-categories as well.
